title: The Next World
author: jazmine
text: my heart stopped.  i stopped breathing.   no one was around.  i felt lonely.  i was only a shadow.   no one saw me.  not really.  i felt i was in a cave a dark cave that no one was in like i was the last person on own planet.  like i had no friends or family.  the sun never came out.  there was no food no water no nothing.   soon i started to wither and die but soon the sun will come out.  i don't no what will happen.  after a few days the sun did come out and i did not want to go.   there were others now.  i was afraid to go out.  i was used to it just being me.  the others were like babies in my old life.  they were little but soon started to grow they grew fast.  now the sun is out even more than before i want to go but i just can't get myself to do it.  i try finally i am in the light no longer afraid.  i have friends and people like family.  it is a lot like my old life but now i have a new life.

title: Night Time In the Garden
author: jennifer
text: the moon has fallen,  every thing is quiet,  but not our nocturnal friends.  the flowers seem dead. . .  but they are alive just tired like we us.  the animals hunt for food to feed their families.  high  up in the tree is a happy bird family.  in the tree is a beautiful squirrel family storing their nuts.  under the soft covers of the earth you can find. . .  moles, worms and other creatures.  as the moon shines bright you are safe in you room lying on your bed under those warm covers. . . .  you might say you are similar to some animals.

title: A Dream That Will Not Come True
author: jennifer
text: i believe that there will once be a day,  when everyone and everything will be perfect.  flowers will blossom,  fresh air without the pollution,  a day that is neither cold or hot,  this will be a perfect day.   this is a day where there will be peace in the world.  children will be laughing,  without every child falling,  scraping a knee,  a elbow,  or arm,  this will be a perfect day.   this is a dream that will not come true,  for there is no such thing as a perfect day,  'cause its only a dream.  a dream that will not come true.  you may believe in a perfect day,  i did and so can you.  a perfect day.  a perfect day!

title: Darkness
author: jessica
text: sadness and darkness are natural siblings.   since ancient times,  people have shown black to express their grief.  happiness is attracted to sunshine as depression is to darkness.  there is a romance in darkness and melancholy.   there is something mysterious about that which is undiscovered as it is unknown.    friends have troubles the problems travel my way sadness comes along with them with friends brings my sadness  time stops and stands still each day  seems like a year i'm lost  and can't be found in this darkness i lay dying cold empty pressured and alone it holds me down and won't let go there is no escaping it consumes me until there's nothing left i may look fine but on the inside i'm full of sadness i get a funny feeling,  it comes from deep inside.  i get all depressed and sad,  wanting to go and hide.  but the thoughts and feelings,  no one will ever be able to see.  people say i'm weird when i'm home it's like i'm a different person,  and the old me just disappeared.  when i hear others sadness it pressures me  the depression of it forces me to cry i whip myself dry followed by repeatedly feeling sad i wish they could get help,  i wish it would go away.  maybe if i keep praying real hard,  it will some day.  they describe the crimson red that fills the cuts i think i'm going to be sick.   with every thing spinning so fast i can barely breath walls closing in and everything fades fashes of light come by i get sleepy and forgetful not knowing myself there it is the worst part worrying i won't see them tomorrow  laying here wondering if you're okay i open my eyes and see flashes of you and me from before you tried  i text you and wait for an answer.   i hear my small light breaths and tears hit my pillow when i get no answer  i text for help can't get the police involved or they'll hate me forever it's the emotional pain that kind that makes your knees go weak and your body shake  when you still get no answer oh god,  is all you can think.  i can barely move a cold chill comes over me i finally get a reply  everything's okay.   just a false alarm as it is almost every night

title: Night Flower

title: The Moment of a Leaf
author: jessica
text: a strong,  crisp autumn wind blows true.  released i am from my part of the branch.  softly,  softly i float down,  everything around me mute.  it seems the forest has gone into a trance.  the birds in my old treetop cease their singing.  the sky is higher than before; the clouds too.  down below my kin are mingling,  something that i will too do.  the ground is getting closer,  closer to me.  my brothers' bodies are of deep and light brown.  from afar,  this i could see.  i softly,  softly hit the soft,  cool soil,  which is the ground.  the forest around me seems to let out a sigh.  do i except my new home and fate? through my siblings shines a new sliver of sunlight.  yes,  this is my new home as of late.

title: The Threads Of Your Life
author: jillian
text: the threads of your life  take the threads of your life,  and weave them into beautiful patterns.  connect them to your past,  your present,  and your hopes and dreams of the future.  make them your own.  express yourself as much as you can.  your opinion is valued.  every voice counts.  take your goals and make them happen.  grab every opportunity in your reach.  and if there are none,   create them.  look at the world in a new perspective every day.  if you love with all your heart,   and spread smiles,  you will spread joy.  so pick up your threads and weave.

text: usually,  i love summer,  but look now,  summers a bummer.  my best friend is moving away,  not a thing that can make her stay.  i didnt catch that one boy's eye,  maybe i was just too shy.  i rekindled a friendship; then broke it down.  acted like a big dumb clown.  but i guess things sorta did ascend,  with new strangers i did befriend.  so many insiders; so many jokes,  they paid for me when i was broke.  yet still i wish school would go on so my old friend will not be gone.  i ignored her; one big silent fight,  until that dreadful hallloween night.  she said she were to move away,  some time after the last school day.  inside i sobbed and bawled and cried but outside i stood and let out a sigh.  now she thinks i dont mind at all,  but really i've tripped into one long fall.  i blame myself for being a jerk.  i wish our friendship would still work.  it's like i've chipped off a huge chunk,  everytime i fix it; falls of with a clunk,  i'm not sure if that chunk is big any more,  'cause i tried my hardest not to ignore.  so friend,  i hope i'm not uncouth,  because i luv ya, and that's the truth.

title: Shoes

title: Beauty

text: what is real beauty? is it a sunset or a rainbow? no,  those are to cheesy.  is it a pretty blonde with a slim figure? no,  thatâ’s too ordanairy.  beauty is not necessarily what most people think it is.  its hidden in the most unlikely places,  and can last  for just a minute or an entire life time.  its not always perfect,  in fact  most imperfections are more beautiful than the perfect things.  people get so caught up looking at a red rose that they fail to see the jagged thorns on the stem.  those thorns protect the flower and keep it alive,  and thatâ’s the true beauty of the entire plant.  a lot of people go their entire life without seeing something truly beautiful.  but thatâ’s because their not looking in the right place.

title: The Unlucky Horseshoe
author: josie
text: one day as i was walking along the street i looked down to find something at my feet  it was a rusty old horseshoe i thought maybe it could be a clue  how lucky! i picked up the horseshoe all rusty and yucky  but my luck changed very quickly indeed i woke up the next morning to find  my alarm clock at 8:15 oh no! iâ’m going to be late!  i glanced out the window to see that it was raining i missed the bus and had to walk to school  i was 20 minutes late i forgot to write my essay for homework  i got detention in one of my classes because my dog ate my homework and i fell in a mud puddle at recess  i tripped on my shoelace and accidentally slammed my finger in the door  when i got home my mom accidentally stepped on my favorite video game and my turtle winky died  so you see that these things donâ’t happen regularly so i have made my decision  i will give the horseshoe to my little brother he needs more than me!

title: The Gingle Gog
author: josie
text: beware of the gingle gog,   that smells like a horrible hog,  it lurks through the murky bog,   and breathes out smelly fog.    for when i was in the boggy bay,   it got too dark for me to play,  so i sat down on some hay,   then i heard a person say:  ''the gingle gog is on the loose,  i saw it eating a goose,  so run and hide,  before it eats you all alive!  so i ran,  but i was too late,   i didn't make it to my gate,   the gingle gog began to roar,   so loud,  that my ears were sore.   i looked at the monster and i almost fainted,   it's skin almost looked painted,   it was the color of a pine tree,   both brown and green.  his fingers were cactuses,  it wasn't hard to see.   the eyes on the body were as big as the moon,   pure white irises shone through,   it had the mouth of a whirlpool in the sea,   sucking up everything like a leech.   it didn't have a noise,   in the arms,  i could see bones.   i ran and i ran,  throughout the land.  it caught up and grabbed me,  but i fought back,   that is the story of my gingle gog attack.

title: Changing
author: judy
text: changing has two sides,  like people.  changing is painful,  changing makes you proud.  it was the first time i felt it,  in forth grade.  like being closed in a dark chamber,  trapped,  alone.  it was like i was being torn apart and that life was dark,  when i had to leave my friend.  when he said good-bye,  with the look in his eyes,  it was like he said my death sentence.  i changed,  he changed.  i thought it was a nightmare,  like when a caterpillar becomes a deformed butterfly.  i thought i would never,  ever have the feeling of having fun,  having a good time,  at first.  then things changed,  like the birth of a new star.  life started again,  and i have friends.  getting out of the dark chamber feels great.

title: When she Left
author: julia
text: youâ’ve been the fabric of my existence,   that has sewn us together for so long.   but once you left we came to the end of the spool.  i wish we could be sown together again,  but…  all the fabric has fallin apart.  it feelâ’s like thereâ’s only one pea in this pod.  because one of them has fallin out for good.  and i wasnâ’t there that faithful day when one of us went to fall off the vine.  i was at home waiting for a horrible cry.  a cry,  a laugh,  a smile,  pain or misery,  waiting for one of these things to come! and once it did…  i was dead for the words that came from me was oneâ’s i will always dread,   i said,  â“itsâ’ not like she died or anything. â” and she did.  she did and then i realized that the saying,  â“you donâ’t really miss something until itâ’s gone. â” is the truest statement ever created by man! who ever said that knew exactly what he was saying.  because if that wasnâ’t true i wouldnâ’t even be thinking of any of the words iâ’m writing.  i have spent all most every night talking to her but… iâ’ve never an answer.  any answer.  any answer that might even come to mind… one single word coming from her to me.  one salable,  one sound one letter.  i would know iâ’m not talking to air.  if i ever did get an answer i would cherish it for as long as my memory could take it.  even longer then life,  even longer then death,  even longer then an eternity.  no amount of time could sum up what that would be like.  ~grandma july 20,  2003 i will always remember you.

text: i used to be a little kid,  laughing and carefree,  debonair and smiling,  i used to be.   now i have discovered ,  my talents and my fails,  i learn and think and wander,  my new and cluttered trails,  now i am.   dressing up and playing,  with flimsy paper dolls,  taking naps and crawling,  i used to be.   getting older,  getting taller,  school and friends and more,  everythingâ’s so complicated,  now i am.   playing house in preschool,  learning to pour milk,  spilling it on dresses,  i used to be.   i get home from school,  and get myself a snack,  my milk is tamed,  my clothes are clean,  now i am.    observing how my dad,  makes delicios tasteful pancakes,  soon doing it by myself,  i used to be.   knowing what is wrong,  doing what is right,  helping others all i can,  now i am.   everything around me,   whirling,  swirling,  twirling,  iâ’m so confused,  what are these things? i used to be.   looking at my memories,   writing out this poem,  makes me smile at what iâ’ve become,  i used to be,  but now i am.      \t\t\t

title: The Sea
author: julia
text: the water ice cold washing over my feet,  the waves and the rocks are ready to meet,  a crash and a bang of cool ocean spray,  i love the wonderful,  beautiful sea.   the sea lions bark,  the seagulls sing,  the fog horn sounds with a certain ring,  i love the wonderful,  beautiful sea.   the warm grainy sand,  i sift through my hand,  the dogs galloping through the open land,  i love the wonderful,  beautiful sea.   the starfish on rocks,  the puffins in flocks,  makes me happy,  content as can be,  i love the wonderful,  beautiful sea.   in bandon,  this little,  sleepy town,  thereâ’s people with crab traps that sink way down,  everyone's joyful in their little shops,  i love the wonderful,  beautiful sea.   itâ’s getting quite late,   so i order a plate,  of oysters and clams galore,  i love the wonderful,  beautiful sea.   dusk is setting,  and weâ’re all amazed,  at the glorious fire that has set ablaze,  i love the wonderful,  beautiful sea.   we wander to the waterâ’s edge,  and gaze over the water and birds on a ledge,  gaze over these waves,  laced with foam,  i love the wonderful,  beautiful sea.   we walk back over the ringlets of kelp,   dried by the afternoon sun,  the little bugs hop and the dogs both run,  i love the wonderful,  beautiful sea.   the seals are all sleeping,  the crabs have stopped creeping ,  the extravagant sunset has faded away,  i love the wonderful beautiful sea.   before i sleep,   i sit up and think,  thereâ’s no place,  not anyplace iâ’d rather be,  than the wonderful beautiful sea.

title: Know-It-All
author: julia
text: every day i go to school,  and i get an a.  i study hard,  and i learn,  in every single way.  things come easily to me,  i have some sort of power.   everything i want to know,  i know within an hour.  i am worshiped by some people,  the ones that canâ’t understand.  â“where is my homework?â” they might ask,  i say,  â“itâ’s in your hand. â” they stare at me with google eyes,  they tug and push then tow.  â“come and help me!â” they will beg.  â“thereâ’s some things i need to know!â”  when i get home i remind my brother,  â“donâ’t jump on the couch! donâ’t slide on the floor,  donâ’t slurp your food,  remember not to slouch!â” all these things i have found out,  and i really must say.  i think an important thing to know,  is how i must obey.  brother gets sent to his room,  for doing all that stuff.  while i sit down and lounge around,  and pull out the pillow fluff.  then when my mother comes downstairs,  after the bitter scolding.  i use all the things i know,  and turn to laundry folding.  see now,  itâ’s not half bad,   it just goes to show.  that if you have this unlucky power,  you will really know!

title: A Gust of Wind
author: julianna
text: a gust of wind blows through the yard,  sweeping up all of the leaves and twirling them around in a circle of wonder,   picking up dirt and other particles that dare to enter in this circle.  the gust of wind mellows down and all of the leaves are now in place.   a gust of wind blows through the yard,  moving the trees branches back and forth as if dancing with each other,  one by one the colorful,  serene birds pick up their legs,  spread out their wings,  and lift in to the air.  a gust of wind blows through the yard,  little kids jump in the leaves and then leap up into the air to escape the leaves from tickling them,   smelling the cool,  crisp air,  they take a deep breath in and fall back into the leaves.   a gust of wind blows through the yard,   keeping the flowers cool from being baked like a cake in the intense heat of the fall sun,   refreshing them for just a moment and then watching the sun keep them warm.   a gust of wind blows through the yard,  swishing the bright and bold american flag back and forth,  as if to say how proud we are to live in this country,  still swaying in the wind,  the flag stands tall and proud,  it will never stop blowing.   a gust of wind blows through the yard.  the water in the pond where the birds bathe and sip ripples.  the ripples look like a butterfly in flight,   the ripples get bigger and bigger and then slow down.   a gust of wind no longer blows through the yard,  everything is silent,  everything is still,  everything is peaceful.  everything is just like the way it was before the wind started to run.  peaceful.  still.  silent.

title: My Own Reflection
author: julie
text: i look into the mirror.  the mirror with the wood frame.  my mirror.  and what do i see? a different angle of me.  itâ’s dark and lonely,  so different then before.  i wonder what happened as i fall to the floor.  i used to always be happy.  no problems or fears.  what do you do when your lost? what do you do when you donâ’t even know yourself? some days i feel like my soul has been stolen and placed high on a shelf.  i must keep waiting for the day when i can reach that high.  i often forget who i am.  i may even be a lie to myself.  you donâ’t really know me.  yes,  thatâ’s a fact.  and you may not believe it.  but all i might be is an act.  iâ’m afraid to show myself in the fear of reflection.  itâ’s strange how these thoughts all came from my reflection.

title: A True Friend
author: julie
text: i have a friend.  she is perfect for me.  she listens to my problems.  as dumb and stupid they may be.  she likes herself for who she is.  and never tries to change.  she could be shy on the phone.  but calls me every night.  talking.  talking.  talking for hours.  mainly about nothing at all.  talking about love and life and school and what we want to be when we grow up.  she knew just how i felt.  she knew how happy i could be.  she listens to me patiently.  she helps me with all my problems.  i don't think i've once judged her.  she never once judged me.  only in our fights and battles.  we've had those many times.  she's such a good friend that we always get back together the next day.  my friend never tells people mean or nasty things about me.  she makes me elated instead of melancholy.  she doesn't spread the word around like a bee.  if only i could have a friend like this,  she would be as happy as me.

title: I love you
author: karina
text: i love you so much,  it is hard to say in words how much i love you.  but,  what i can say is that you mean a lot to me  you are the  cold popsicle i need on a summer day,  you are the   feeling you get christmas morning,  you are the  big bite into a cupcake,  you are the new american girl doll i always wanted.   i think of it as… i am the body of the plane  and you are my wings.   you help me get places and you guide me through it safely.  without the wings i'd only stay up a little bit then i'd fall right back down.   you always help me right back up when i fall.   then we laugh together but not any laugh,  not the laugh you force out to be polite   a true laugh.   whenever i am with you  i feel so open like i could fly.   that is how much i love you
